The evidence with the title 'The 5 things the Republican Congress will get done — or at least try to ' says Jan 2, 2017  ... It is no secret that Republicans would like to “restructure” Medicare, the government's program to cover seniors' health care, and Medicaid, which covers low-income people, in order to reduce the programs' costs. Medicare and Medicaid cost over $1 trillion in 2016 and cover more than 120 million people. 
